                  <msItem>
                     <p> Deed, by which <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Wade</surname>, notary public</persName>, and
               others, attest an agreement made 16 March, <origDate when="1362">1362</origDate>, between 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Sarah</forename> de <surname>Hales</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_104458">Norwich</placeName>
                        </persName> 
               and <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename>, prior of the <orgName role="prior" key="org_104033">Holy Trinity church, Norwich</orgName>
                        </persName>, 
               by which the said Sarah, in consideration of an allowance as a corrody and the performance of an obit for
               <persName>
                           <forename>Nigel</forename> de <surname>Hales</surname>
                        </persName> her husband and sir <pb n="200"/>
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Eton</surname>, priest</persName>, deceased, grants to the
               said prior and convent all her buildings or tenements in the parish of 
               <placeName key="place_104556">St. Peter, Houndegate</placeName>, and 2Â½ acres of land lying without the gates of 
               <placeName type="street" key="place_104162">Fybriggate</placeName>, except one messuage opposite to the gates of her mansion,
               and one long house near the same, which she grants to 
               <persName>sir <forename>Hugh</forename>, then rector of <placeName role="rector" key="place_104556">St. Peter, Houndegate</placeName>
                        </persName>. 
               Deed promulgated by <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename> 
                           <surname>Stoket</surname>, official of <persName>
                              <forename>Henry</forename>, bishop of <placeName type="diocese" role="person" key="place_101090">Norwich</placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
               3 March, <origDate when="1395">1395</origDate>, 
               and <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> 
                           <surname>Jakkes</surname>, rector of <placeName role="rector" key="place_104556">St. Peter, Houndegate</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               made a party to it.  </p>
